<br>
But, truthfully, any race except ogre.  Ogre is overdone and too many have the same intellect as their character does.  There are some good ogre warriors out there, but far too many aren't.  Gnome is nice, don't need a shrink on raids, and are very rare.  Plus get epics and a robe, and look like yoda.  Dwarf is nice and my personal favorite, but there are too many of us out there also, and a good portion aren't as high quality.  Elves will get made fun of a lot, but they aren't bad.  Really, the rare races make the best tanks I've seen, since they have had to prove themselves in the past.<br>
Slam isn't a huge deal, can ghetto bash if you feel you need it.<br>
Unstunability from the front, meh meh meh.<br>
Fitting in places without buying potions, or bringing along a shaman (since cobalt bracers don't work til 46) is something I like.<br>
<br>
In the end, the best warrior race is the one you like the most.  The best warriors are based on who's behind the character, not what the character is. <p>Veteran Overdorf <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18306">Hussar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Kneeslicer - Drunken Tsunami</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mohenjo>Mohenjo </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/03 3:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3075.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   omg</span><hr size=1> humans warriors are by far the sexAest in the game. <br>
