<br>
But if you DO wanna look at race in that way, the races in terms of starting stats go like this:<br>
<br>
Ogre, Troll, Barb, Dwarf, Vah Shir, Human, and the rest are about the same after that.<br>
<br>
A great advantage of the smaller races is that they can fit in places larger races cannot.  They never have to worry about getting a shrink.  Ogre's have to get shrunk just to exp in many old world dungeons like Solusek or Runnyeye.  Plus in the end game, all large races have to shrunk during raids to make it easier for people to move around.  <br>
<br>
But what really matters is the race you like most.  <br>
<br>
Oh, and btw, Dwarf &gt; All =D   <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:copperplate gothic light;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>They come like sacrifices in their trim, <br>
